</P>
<P>
   ``TREND WATCH: PEARL PARTY.'' From WWD. Three color slides. When
it comes to classics, nothing beats pearls. And this season,
jewelry designers are making them current again. A pictorial.
</P>
<P>
   ``BEAUTY TREND: NEUTRAL TERRITORY.'' From W magazine. One color
slide. We always suspected Catherine Deneuve was on to something.
What started as a mere trendlet at the fall ready-to-wear
collections _ the ultra-sexy, Belle de Jour-era nude mouth _
emerged as a fullblown trend at the fall couture. A report.
</P>
<P>
   ``MILAN IN MOTION.'' A guide to the top fashion shows of Milan.
On the catwalk: Emporio Armani, Dolce &AMP; Gabbana, Fendi, Ferragamo,
Gianfranco Ferre, Gucci, Prada, Narciso Rodriguez, Jil Sander and
Versus, among others.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BUSINESS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``E-TAILING GETS FASHIONABLE.'' From WWD. Apparel marketers are
starting to spin a fashion web on the Internet. The concept that
cyberspace is a viable sales ground only for basic styles and
commodity items rather than trendy designs was solidly debunked by
a range of manufacturers and retailers at a roundtable discussion
in New York last week. A report.
</P>
