</P>
<P>
   Population: 164 million
</P>
<P>
   Area: 3,286,000 square miles
</P>
<P>
   Language: Portuguese
</P>
<P>
   Currency: the Real
</P>
<P>
   Religion: Predominantly Catholic
</P>
<P>
   President: Fernando Henrique Cardoso, re-elected to a second
term Oct. 4.
</P>
<P>
   Background: Cardoso, 67, is a former sociologist. He is also a
former foreign minister and finance minister. He designed the Real
Plan, a measure that stabilized the currency and brought inflation
down to near zero from 3,000 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Government: The 1988 constitution provides for a bicameral
legislature that has 81 seats in the Senate and 503 seats in the
Chamber of Deputies. Congressional elections are held every four
years.
</P>
