<HEADLINE>
DON'T FRET OVER BREAKFAST; FIX FRITTATE 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By ANN STEINER 
and CICI WILLIAMSON 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   On weekday mornings, it's a bowl of cereal and out the door.
Weekend breakfasts are more leisurely. But even for the joyful
cook, there's no reason to waste precious time in the kitchen.
</P>
<P>
   Making frittate _ Italy's answer to omelets _ takes mere minutes
in the microwave without sacrificing the superior taste of a dish
that takes longer to cook conventionally.
</P>
<P>
   And the results are lush. Creamy eggs hold enticing chunks of
whatever one chooses to add. As with omelets, one usual addition is
cheese, which can be the cook's choice.
</P>
<P>
   A new cheese we like is Snofrisk (``snow fresh''), a goat cheese
for beginners. Those who shy from the somewhat barnyard overtones
of cheese made solely from goat's milk will like this Norwegian
variety from the producers of Jarlsberg. It contains 20 percent
cow's milk.
</P>
<P>
   For those restricting cholesterol, frittate can be made from egg
substitutes. One large fresh egg contains 215 milligrams
cholesterol; Simply Eggs (containing yolks) has 45 milligrams; Egg
Beaters (egg whites) contains none.
</P>
<P>
   Egg substitutes are packaged in cartons like half-pints of milk.
An unopened carton can be stored in the refrigerator several weeks.
For best results, use by the date on the carton. After opening, use
within three days. To substitute Simply Eggs or Egg Beaters for
whole fresh eggs, use \ cup for each large egg in a recipe.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Spicy Herb and Cheese Frittata Wedges
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (4-ounce) can chopped green chilies &QL;
</P>
<P>
   cup mixed shredded Colby and Cheddar cheeses &QL; 
{ cup crumbled feta cheese (2 ounces) &QL; 
6 eggs &QL; 
2 tablespoons torn fresh basil leaves or 1 teaspoon dried &QL; 
\ teaspoon salt &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Spray an 8-inch round baking dish with nonstick spray. Scatter
green chilies in bottom of dish and top with mixed cheeses and
feta. In a small mixing bowl, beat eggs with basil and salt. Pour
egg mixture over all.
</P>
<P>
   Cover dish with wax paper. Rotating dish every 3 minutes,
microwave on medium-high (70 percent) 10 to 12 minutes or until
center jiggles only slightly. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before
cutting into wedges.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 6 servings, each: 148 calories, 12 grams protein, 10 grams
fat, 3 grams carbohydrates, 1 gram fiber, 230 milligrams
cholesterol, 381 milligrams sodium. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Goat Cheese Frittata
</P>
<P>
   1 (4.4-ounce) package Snofrisk goat cheese &QL; 
6 eggs &QL; 
2 cups diced zucchini &QL; 
1 cup diced red bell pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   cup chopped, pitted black olives (about 15) &QL; 
\ teaspoon freshly ground pepper &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In a mixing bowl, whisk together cheese and eggs, taking care to
leave some lumps of cheese; set aside.
</P>
<P>
   Spray an 8-inch round baking dish with nonstick spray. Add
zucchini and bell pepper; cover with wax paper. Stirring after 2
minutes, microwave on high 4 minutes. Stir in olives and pepper;
stir in egg mixture; re-cover.
</P>
<P>
   Microwave on high 3 minutes. Stir cooked edges into the center.
Re-cover and microwave on high 2 to 3 minutes, or until center
jiggles only slightly. Cool a few minutes before cutting into 6
wedges.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 6 servings, each: 150 calories, 11 grams protein, 10 grams
fat, 4 grams carbohydrates, 1 gram fiber, 222 milligrams
cholesterol, 211 milligrams sodium. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Less-Cholesterol Spinach Frittata
</P>
<P>
   1 (10-ounce) package frozen chopped spinach &QL; 
1 cup Simply Eggs or egg substitute &QL;
</P>
<P>
   cup low-fat milk &QL; 
{ teaspoon salt &QL; 
\ teaspoon nutmeg &QL; 
[ teaspoon cayenne pepper &QL; 
1 cup part-skim, reduced-fat, shredded mozzarella cheese &QL; 
2 crosswise slices red bell pepper &QL; 
Paprika &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Spray an 8-inch round glass dish or 9-inch pie plate with
vegetable coating; set aside. Place package of frozen spinach on a
paper towel. Microwave on high 5 minutes; set aside.
</P>
<P>
   Pour Simply Eggs into a 4-cup glass measure. Beat in milk, then
salt, nutmeg and cayenne. Stir in cheese. Squeeze package of
spinach to remove as much moisture as possible. Add spinach to egg
mixture.
</P>
<P>
   Pour spinach mixture into prepared dish. Garnish with bell
pepper slices and paprika; cover with wax paper. Microwave on
medium-high (70 percent) 10 to 12 minutes, rotating dish every 3
minutes, until center jiggles only slightly. Let stand 5 to 10
minutes before serving.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 4 servings, each: 178 calories, 15 grams protein, 10 grams
fat, 7 grams carbohydrates, 3 grams fiber, 68 milligrams
cholesterol, 679 milligrams sodium. &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXEND OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
