<HEADLINE>
SOLD ON `I'LL BUY THAT,' IF YOU CAN FIND IT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I recently heard about a book, ``I'll Buy That'' by Tony
Hyman, that lists collectors around the country. Bookstores say
that it is out of print and unavailable. Is there any way to get
one?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.J., Benbrook, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: That 1989 book has been revised several times. Hyman
recommends the current edition, which has been renamed as the
``Trash or Treasure Directory of Buyers.''
</P>
<P>
   The $29.95 book should be available at many bookstores in the
collectibles section. You also can order it directly from the
author by calling (800) 474-6836.
</P>
<P>
   Hyman has a syndicated radio show, ``Trash or Treasure,'' which
airs on weekends. You can listen to it over the Internet at 2 p.m.
CDT Saturay and 9 p.m. CDT Sunday at
www.broadcast.com/radio/talk/ubn.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I've known for years that there was a state prison in Canon
City, Colo. Recently, we went through there and saw another
correctional facility on Highway 50 just east of the city. When was
it built?
</P>
<P>
   _ B.B., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: That's difficult to answer because there are 13 prisons in or
near Canon City, the home to more than 4,500 of the state's 12,800
inmates.
</P>
<P>
   The city of 26,000 has nine state prisons, including the
Arrowhead Correctional Facility, Centennial Correctional Facility,
Colorado State Penitentiary, Colorado Women's Correctional
Facility, Fremont Correctional Facility and Skyline Correctional
Center.
</P>
<P>
   The nearby city of Florence has four federal prisons, including
the maximum-security SuperMax facility that has housed Ted
Kaczynski and Timothy McVeigh.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Isabella Rossellini?
</P>
<P>
   _ R.G., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Rossellini in care of the United Talent Agency, 9560
Wilshire Blvd., Suite 500, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   The 46-year-old actress is the daughter of director Roberto
Rossellini and actress Ingrid Bergman. She has a twin sister,
Ingrid, and recently testified on her behalf when Ingrid's
ex-husband was accused of harassing her.
</P>
<P>
   Isabella's most recent project was the NBC miniseries
``Merlin.''
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
