<SLUG> BC-LEAGUE-FOOD3-3ndtake-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHICKEN AND BROCCOLI STIR-FRY WITH CASHEWS
</HEADLINE>
 
LOS ANGELES: Makes 4 servings. 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)
<TEXT>
<P>
   SESAME COOKING SAUCE:
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup water
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon dry sherry
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon sesame oil
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon cornstarch
</P>
<P>
   MARINADE:
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons cornstarch
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons dry sherry
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons water
</P>
<P>
   Dash white pepper
</P>
<P>
   CHICKEN STIR-FRY:
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into
bite-size pieces
</P>
<P>
   3 1/2 tablespoons vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup cashews
</P>
<P>
   1 small clove garlic, minced
</P>
<P>
   3 cups broccoli florets
</P>
<P>
   1 cup julienned carrots
</P>
<P>
   1/2 large onion, cut into wedges
</P>
<P>
   For Sesame Cooking Sauce, in a small bowl, combine water,
sherry, soy sauce, sugar, oil and cornstarch.
</P>
<P>
   For Marinade, in another bowl, combine soy sauce, cornstarch,
sherry, water and white pepper.
</P>
<P>
   For Chicken Stir-Fry, add chicken to marinade; toss to coat.
Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons oil. Marinate 15 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   In a wok or large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-low
heat. Add cashews. Toast until golden; remove from wok. Increase
heat to high; add 2 teaspoons oil. Add garlic when oil is hot,
stirring once. Add chicken. Stir-fry 3 minutes or until chicken is
opaque. Remove from wok. Add remaining oil to wok. Add broccoli,
carrots and onion. Stir-fry 3 minutes, adding a few drops of water,
if wok appears dry.
</P>
<P>
   Return chicken and cashews to wok. Stir in Sesame Cooking Sauce.
Cook until sauce bubbles and thickens and chicken is cooked
through, stirring constantly. Serve with rice. Makes 6 servings.
</P>
<P>
   SALMON IN PASTRY CRUST &QC;
</P>
<P>
   A great meal for entertaining. Your guests will think you worked
for hours.
</P>
<P>
   1 salmon fillet (12 to 18 inches long, 4 to 6 inches wide)
</P>
<P>
   1 package (17 1/4 ounces) frozen chopped puff pastry sheets
</P>
<P>
   1 package (10 ounces) frozen chopped spinach, thawed and
squeezed dry
</P>
<P>
   1/2 to 3/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese
</P>
<P>
   1/2 to 3/4 cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   Water
</P>
<P>
   1 egg
</P>
<P>
   Place salmon in center of a pastry sheet.
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, combine spinach, Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper. Spread over salmon.
</P>
<P>
   Cover salmon and spinach with remaining pastry sheet. Moisten
edges of pastry with water; seal top and bottom, pressing gently
with a fork. Trim off excess. Cut leaves and other designs from
excess pastry.
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, beat together egg and 1 tablespoon water. Brush egg
wash over pastry. Poke a few holes in pastry using a fork. Place on
a baking sheet.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 30 to 45 minutes or until
golden brown. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   RED PEPPER PASTA &QC;
</P>
<P>
   3 large red bell peppers, cut into thin strips
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons minced garlic
</P>
<P>
   8 tablespoons olive oil
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   Water
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 pounds uncooked linguine
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups chopped onions
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup coarsely chopped walnuts, toasted
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup chopped fresh parsley
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups grated Parmesan cheese
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl, combine bell peppers, garlic and 6 1/2
tablespoons oil. Season with salt and pepper. Marinate, covered, at
room temperature 2 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Fill a large pot with salted water and bring to a boil over high
heat. Add linguine. Cook until al dente; drain.
</P>
<P>
   Warm remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in a large heavy skillet,
over medium heat. Add onions. Saute 6 minutes or until tender and
brown. Stir in bell pepper mixture. Saute 4 minutes. Add pasta;
toss to coat.
</P>
<P>
   Remove to a serving bowl. Add walnuts, parsley and Parmesan
cheese; toss to coat. Makes 6 servings.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: Bell peppers may be marinated in a covered container in
refrigerator up to 12 hours. Pine nuts may be substituted for
walnuts.
</P>
<P>
   CHOCOLATE CHIP COFFEECAKE &QC;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups semisweet chocolate chips
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup packed light brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 cup coarsely chopped walnuts OR pecans
</P>
<P>
   2 cups flour
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon baking powder
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   1 cup dairy sour cream
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup butter, softened
</P>
<P>
   1 cup granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   2 eggs
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   Coat a 9-inch springform pan with nonstick cooking spray.
</P>
<P>
   In a small bowl, combine chocolate chips, brown sugar and
walnuts.
</P>
<P>
   In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and
cinnamon.
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl, cream sour cream, butter, granulated sugar and
eggs until blended. Mix in vanilla. Add flour mixture, beating
until thoroughly combined.
</P>
<P>
   Layer batter and chocolate chip mixture, 1/2 at a time, in
prepared springform pan, ending with chocolate chip mixture.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 40 to 45 minutes or until a
wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 10 to 12
servings.
</P>
<P>
   CLASSIC ITALIAN TIRAMISU &QC;
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups espresso OR strong coffee, at room temperature
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup brandy
</P>
<P>
   2 egg yolks
</P>
<P>
   1 pound mascarpone cheese
</P>
<P>
   7 ounces ladyfingers
</P>
<P>
   4 ounces semisweet chocolate, shaved
</P>
<P>
   1 cup whipping cream
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons powdered sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, combine espresso, granulated sugar and brandy,
stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove 1/3 cup to another small
bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Whisk egg yolks into the 1/3 cup espresso mixture. Add
mascarpone cheese and whisk until smooth. Do not over mix.
</P>
<P>
   Line a 5x9-inch loaf pan with wax paper or plastic wrap. Dip
ladyfingers, one at a time, into espresso mixture. Line bottom of
prepared pan with ladyfingers. Layer 1/2 of mascarpone cheese
mixture, 1/2 of chocolate and 1/2 of remaining ladyfingers in loaf
pan. Repeat layering until all ingredients are used, ending with
ladyfingers. Chill, covered with plastic wrap, in refrigerator 6 to
12 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Invert onto a serving plate.
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl, beat cream. Beat in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Use to frost top and sides of tiramisu. Decorate with sifted cocoa,
additional shaved semisweet chocolate and raspberries. Cut in
slices to serve. Keep any leftovers refrigerated. Makes 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   PISTACHIO CHOCOLATE SHORTBREAD &QC;
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup butter, softened
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups flour
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup semisweet chocolate chips
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup coarsely chopped pistachios
</P>
<P>
   1 egg white, beaten
</P>
<P>
   Coat an 8-inch-square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, cream butter and sugar. Mix in vanilla. Stir in
flour, gradually. Fold in chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pistachios.
Spread in pan. Brush lightly with egg white. Sprinkle remaining 1/4
cup pistachios over batter.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 300-degree oven 30 minutes or until lightly
browned. Cool and cut into squares. Makes 16 squares. &UR; !end! &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
