<P>
   AUTO REVIEW-AZR (Undated) _ Four doors, no waiting. That's the
new slogan in the minivan world, where buyers have rebelled against
the right-side-only, sliding-rear-door setup. Now, it's rear doors
on both sides or else. The Nissan Quest/Mercury Villager has been
one of my favorite minivans for years, mainly for its driveability,
especially the carlike handling. For '99, the Quest has been
restyled and updated, with more interior space, a more-powerful
engine, freshened styling and, of course, a second sliding door. By
Bob Golfen.
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-BMW-NYT (Undated) _ A look at BMW's M coupe, the
fastest car the company has ever sold in the United States. A
$42,370 Go Kart with two sport seats and room for two golf bags,
with the kind of razor-edged maneuverability that the company's M
