   CARS-BUYING-NYT (Landover) _ People used to go to auto shows to
see new car models from all companies and then to a particular
dealer to test-drive the one they liked. Now General Motors, eager
to regain market share, is trying a new way to sell cars; it is
putting on its own one-company auto shows, where visitors can take
test drives, to raise the chance that when the customer goes to a
dealer, it will belong to GM. By Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
