   AUTO-REVIEW-BOS (Toronto) _ The new Odyssey is very different
from the old Odyssey _ which isn't exactly old in the grand scheme
of things. In some ways the new Odyssey is different from anything
else on wheels. It is the largest vehicle ever produced by Honda
and, unlike the old Odyssey, it is built on this side of the world,
in a new plant in Alliston, Ont., an hour's drive from downtown
Toronto. The heart of the Odyssey is a 3.5-liter ``variable''
horsepower V-6 mated with a 4-speed automatic transmission.
Variable? With premium-grade fuel, the new engine puts out 210
horsepower; with regular grades, the horsepower drops to 205 _
believe me, you can live with that. By John R. White.
