<HEADER>
A8997 &Cx1f; taf-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RELIGION-ADVISORY-NYT     10-15 0324
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RELIGION-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service calls your attention to the
following religion features moved during the last week.
</P>
<P>
   For retransmission of these stories, call 888-346-9867.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-COLUMN-BOS (Undated) -- Sigmund Freud and C.S. Lewis
are receiving heightened attention because it is the 100th
anniversary of Freud's founding of psychoanalysis and the 100th
anniversary of Lewis' birth. By Diego Ribadeneira.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-PRIESTS-ART-NYT (Rome) _ Young American men entering the
priesthood today are far more conservative and tradition-bound than
many of their elders and most American Roman Catholics, according
to bishops, priests and church surveys. By Alessandra Stanley.
</P>
<P>
   MARRIAGE-EDUC-NYT (Undated) _ As conservatives and liberals
alike have come to agree on the importance of marriage and the need
to strengthen families, a growing number of high schools across the
country are requiring students to undergo marriage education. The
movement to teach relationship skills, however, is only part of a
growing debate over what, and where, American children should be
taught about love and marriage. Some question the whole concept of
marriage education in the schools, arguing that it is an area best
left to churches and community groups and reserved for adults in a
relationship _ not high-school students. By Tamar Lewin.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-COLUMN-NYT (Undated) _ Just as the White House scandal
involving Monica Lewinsky has left many Americans divided and
angry, so it is becoming an increasingly public matter of
contention among the nation's religious leaders. Within their broad
ranks, the issue is not whether the president did wrong. Instead,
the question many clergy members have been wrestling with is, what
is the pressing moral issue at stake for the nation in the scandal?
By Gustav Niebuhr.
</P>
<P>
   See also also continuing coverage of today's papal encyclical.
