   FED-RATECUT (Washington) _ For the first time in recent memory,
the Federal Reserve changes rates between Fed meetings and cuts
both the short-term and discount rates by .25 percent. By Richard
W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-BANKS (Undated) _ The troubled Russian bond deals in
which Goldman, Sachs was involved _ and the skillful way in which
the firm protected its assets _ provide a window on the role
Goldman and many other investment bankers played in the breathless
rise and fall of the newly liberated Russian economy. A special
report, by Joseph Kahn and Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
