<P>
   FBC-TULANE _ Tulane has been the biggest surprise of the college
football season, winning its first four games and earning its first
national ranking in 19 years. The Green Wave feature a talented
quarterback in Shaun King, last year's Conference USA offensive
player of the year, and a defense that's one of the nation's best.
The team has come together under coach Tommy Bowden, who has won 11
of 15 games since becoming coach in 1997. For a program that had
not had a winning season since 1980, Bowden has worked wonders at
the New Orleans university. But one question arises - how long will
he stay before more established programs come calling? (Lee,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
