   FBC-GATECH-DEFENSE _ Georgia Tech had the worst defense in the
ACC last season and coach George O'Leary brought in a new defensive
coordinator (Randy Edsall) to correct the problem. Through five
games this season, the Jackets are still last in the conference in
total defense. The offense has been carrying the team by scoring 40
points in its four victories, but the defense figures to receive
its first stiff challenge since the opener against Boston College
when Tech hosts No. 7 Virginia Saturday. (C. Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
